
<manpage TITLE="authmon" SECTNUM=8>
<mansect>NAME 
 <P>authmon - authentication monitor



<mansect>SYNOPSIS<P>
<bf>authmon</bf> &lsqb;-d chdir&rsqb; &lsqb;auth2 options&rsqb;<P>


<mansect>DESCRIPTION<P>
<bf>authmon</bf> is the authentication server watchdog process.  If
<em>auth2</em> dies, <bf>authmon</bf> will restart it automatically.

<bf>authmon</bf> supports the following command line arguments:
<descrip>
<tag><bf>-d</bf> <em>chdir</em></tag>Specifies where <bf>authmon</bf>
should run from, and what directory to put log files in.
<P></descrip>

<descrip>
<tag><bf>auth2 options</bf></tag>Valid <em>auth2</em> command line
options.  These options will be passed on to <em>auth2</em> when it is started.
<P></descrip>


<mansect>SEE ALSO<P>
auth2 (8)


